            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This answer is indeed the prefered 4.x way:  &lt;code&gt;$match&lt;/code&gt; to cut down the space, then &lt;code&gt;$filter&lt;/code&gt; to keep what you want, overwriting the input field (use output of &lt;code&gt;$filter&lt;/code&gt; on field &lt;code&gt;shapes&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;$project&lt;/code&gt; back on to &lt;code&gt;shapes&lt;/code&gt;.   Style note:  best not to use the field name as the &lt;code&gt;as&lt;/code&gt; argument because that can lead to confusion later with &lt;code&gt;$$shape&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;$shape&lt;/code&gt;.  I prefer &lt;code&gt;zz&lt;/code&gt; as the &lt;code&gt;as&lt;/code&gt; field because it really stands out.&lt;/span&gt;

